# Do not push local-only content

Never stage, commit, or push any of the following:

- **`Stories/`** — all story folders and their generated HTML/JSON
- **Environment variables** — `.env`, `.env.*`, credentials, secrets (`.env.example` templates only are OK)
- **`inspiring/`** — reference/inspiration code and assets

When committing or pushing, exclude these paths even if they appear modified or untracked. Prefer updating `.gitignore` over adding them to the repo. If they are already tracked, untrack with `git rm --cached` and leave local files intact.
